Updated `content/papers/confidence.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

Summary of changes:
- Added missing blank-line paragraph breaks in clearly merged spots (notably in the introduction) and inserted blank lines before section/subsection headings for cleaner Markdown paragraph boundaries.
- Added KaTeX equation tags `\tag{1}` through `\tag{38}` to display equations so in-text equation references are discoverable and visible.
- Repaired one malformed ASCII/center table (weatherman example) into a standard Markdown table for Hugo rendering.
- Did not change equation expressions, symbols, variables, or mathematical content.
- Did not alter paper meaning/content, and did not remove figures.

Self-check:
- Paragraph boundaries now use blank lines in the edited structural cases.
- In-text equation references that rely on numbered equations in this range are now matched by visible tagged display equations.
